ings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Krahenbuhl was born in 1485, in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William Walford on 4 October 1505, in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 19 April 1547, in her hometown, at the age of 62, and was buried in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1485–19 April 1547":"1485–19. aprill 1547","1441–Male":"1441–Surnud","1515–1565":"1515–1565","1485–1547":"1485–1547","1547":"1547","19 April 1547":"19. aprill 1547","1565":"1565","1485":"1485","1441":"1441","4 October 1505":"4. oktoober 1505","1515":"1515","Myddle, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Myddle, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1485–19 April 1547":"1485–19. huhtikuuta 1547","1441–Male":"1441–Kuollut","1515–1565":"1515–1565","1485–1547":"1485–1547","1547":"1547","19 April 1547":"19. huhtikuuta 1547","1565":"1565","1485":"1485","1441":"1441","4 October 1505":"4. lokakuuta 1505","1515":"1515","Myddle, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Myddle, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1485–19 April 1547":"1485–19 avril 1547","1441–Male":"1441–Décédé","1515–1565":"1515–1565","1485–1547":"1485–1547","1547":"1547","19 April 1547":"19 avril 1547","1565":"1565","1485":"1485","1441":"1441","4 October 1505":"4 octobre 1505","1515":"1515","Myddle, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Myddle, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Shropshire, England, United Ki